## 1) Cloud Computing Fundamentals

### Q1
Which statement best describes cloud computing?

A. Buying physical servers for permanent use  
B. Delivering computing services over the internet  
C. Installing software only on local devices  
D. Running workloads without any network

**Answer:** B

### Q2
Which cloud model provides resources over the internet and is owned by a cloud provider?

A. Private cloud  
B. Public cloud  
C. Hybrid cloud  
D. Edge cloud

**Answer:** B

### Q3
A company wants to keep some workloads on-premises and move others to Azure. Which model fits best?

A. Public cloud  
B. Private cloud  
C. Hybrid cloud  
D. SaaS

**Answer:** C

### Q4
Which cloud model is most suitable when strict data residency or regulatory requirements require dedicated infrastructure?

A. Public cloud  
B. Private cloud  
C. Hybrid cloud  
D. Community SaaS

**Answer:** B

### Q5
What is a key financial benefit of cloud computing?

A. High upfront capital expense (CapEx)  
B. Predictable hardware refresh cycles  
C. Shift from CapEx to operational expense (OpEx)  
D. No billing model

**Answer:** C

---

## 2) Benefits of Cloud Services

### Q6
What does **high availability** mean in cloud computing?

A. Resources can only scale up  
B. Services remain available despite failures  
C. Resources are always on-premises  
D. Data is stored in one datacenter

**Answer:** B

### Q7
What is **scalability**?

A. Automatically distributing users to a support team  
B. Ability to increase or decrease resources to meet demand  
C. Encrypting all storage by default  
D. Migrating all apps to containers

**Answer:** B

### Q8
What is **elasticity** in cloud computing?

A. Paying annually for fixed resources  
B. Automatically scaling resources in/out as demand changes  
C. Running workloads only at night  
D. Moving data to tape backups

**Answer:** B

### Q9
Which benefit refers to confidence that cloud costs and performance can be forecasted?

A. Security  
B. Governance  
C. Predictability  
D. Reliability

**Answer:** C

### Q10
Which benefit helps ensure standards and policies are consistently applied to resources?

A. Manageability  
B. Governance  
C. Elasticity  
D. Fault tolerance

**Answer:** B

### Q11
Which cloud benefit allows admins to monitor resources through portals, APIs, and automation tools?

A. Reliability  
B. Manageability  
C. Availability  
D. Performance tuning

**Answer:** B

### Q12
Which benefit is most directly improved by distributing applications across multiple regions?

A. CapEx reduction  
B. Reliability and resilience  
C. Local disk performance only  
D. Software licensing

**Answer:** B

---

## 3) Cloud Service Types (IaaS, PaaS, SaaS)

### Q13
Which cloud service model provides the most control over operating systems and networking?

A. SaaS  
B. PaaS  
C. IaaS  
D. FaaS

**Answer:** C

### Q14
In which model does the cloud provider manage the runtime, middleware, and OS, while you manage your app and data?

A. IaaS  
B. PaaS  
C. SaaS  
D. Private cloud

**Answer:** B

### Q15
Which service model typically requires the least technical management by the customer?

A. IaaS  
B. PaaS  
C. SaaS  
D. Hybrid cloud

**Answer:** C

### Q16
Which is the best example of SaaS?

A. Creating virtual machines in Azure  
B. Deploying code to a managed web app platform  
C. Using Microsoft 365 email service  
D. Configuring virtual networks

**Answer:** C

### Q17
You want to deploy web apps quickly without patching operating systems. Which model fits best?

A. IaaS  
B. PaaS  
C. SaaS  
D. On-premises only

**Answer:** B

### Q18
You need full control over VM OS settings for a legacy application. Which model should you choose?

A. SaaS  
B. PaaS  
C. IaaS  
D. Serverless only

**Answer:** C

