## 4) Shared Responsibility Model

### Q19
In all cloud models, who is always responsible for data and account identities?

A. Cloud provider only  
B. Customer only  
C. Both share equally in every exact task  
D. Third-party auditor

**Answer:** B

### Q20
Under SaaS, which responsibility is mostly handled by the cloud provider?

A. Physical datacenter security  
B. Customer data classification  
C. User access decisions  
D. Compliance ownership for customer data

**Answer:** A

### Q21
Compared to IaaS, customer responsibility in PaaS is generally:

A. Higher  
B. Lower  
C. Exactly the same  
D. Not defined

**Answer:** B

### Q22
In IaaS, who typically patches and maintains the guest operating system?

A. Cloud provider  
B. Customer  
C. Hardware vendor  
D. Nobody

**Answer:** B

### Q23
Which statement is true about shared responsibility?

A. The provider is always responsible for everything  
B. The customer is always responsible for physical servers  
C. Responsibility depends on the service model (IaaS/PaaS/SaaS)  
D. It applies only to networking

**Answer:** C

---

## 5) Pricing and Consumption Concepts

### Q24
What does **consumption-based pricing** mean?

A. Pay a fixed amount regardless of usage  
B. Pay only for resources used  
C. Buy hardware every 3 years  
D. No billing visibility

**Answer:** B

### Q25
Which is a common cloud cost optimization approach?

A. Overprovision all resources permanently  
B. Use reserved capacity/pricing where appropriate  
C. Disable monitoring  
D. Avoid autoscaling

**Answer:** B

### Q26
Why is cloud often considered more agile than traditional datacenter procurement?

A. Hardware shipping is faster  
B. Resources can be provisioned on demand  
C. Procurement approvals are removed  
D. Networking is unnecessary

**Answer:** B

### Q27
Which concept helps avoid paying for idle infrastructure in many workloads?

A. Fixed annual licensing  
B. Elastic scaling  
C. Air-gapped deployment  
D. Manual capacity planning only

**Answer:** B

---

## 6) Scenario Questions

### Q28
A startup expects traffic spikes during marketing campaigns but low traffic otherwise. What is the best cloud advantage?

A. CapEx-heavy purchasing  
B. Elasticity and pay-as-you-go  
C. Single-server architecture  
D. Static allocation forever

**Answer:** B

### Q29
A bank must keep sensitive workloads on dedicated internal infrastructure, but wants cloud scalability for public apps. Which model fits?

A. Public cloud  
B. Private cloud only  
C. Hybrid cloud  
D. SaaS only

**Answer:** C

### Q30
A team wants the provider to manage OS and runtime while they focus on code. Which service type should they choose?

A. IaaS  
B. PaaS  
C. SaaS  
D. Bare metal hosting

**Answer:** B

### Q31
A company needs to quickly provide virtual servers with full admin access. Which model is best?

A. SaaS  
B. PaaS  
C. IaaS  
D. DaaS only

**Answer:** C

### Q32
Your organization wants to reduce datacenter maintenance burden while still using standard business applications like email and collaboration tools. Which model is most suitable?

A. IaaS  
B. PaaS  
C. SaaS  
D. Private cloud only

**Answer:** C

